"{\"uid\": \"sundayworld.com-crime-world-crime-australian-woman-gang-raped-by-five-men-in-paris-days-before-the-olympics-reports-a445119463.html\", \"text\": \"Neil Fetherstonhaugh  A major police investigation is reportedly underway after an Australian woman was allegedly gang raped by five men in Paris just days before the Olympics.  It has been reported that the 25-year-old woman was attacked in the French capital on Saturday morning at about 5am.  Local media reports that the victim sought refuge in a kebab shop, located just metres from the Moulin Rouge on the Boulevard de Clinchy in the city's 18th arrondissement, following the incident.  She was later transferred to Bichat Hospital by paramedics who came to her assistance.  The incident had also been reported on Australian 7News whose reporter Ash Mullany revealed that the woman, according to several French media outlets, \\\"went inside with her dress on back to front and it was reportedly torn,\\\" Mullany said.  \\\"She told police she had been raped by five men. Now, this woman was taken to a local hospital. It was there she underwent a medical examination.  \\\"It's alleged this happened over the weekend, in the early hours of Saturday morning.\\\"  According to the report, the woman, who had been planning to travel back to Australia, is now remaining in Paris to help police with their investigation.  A number of officers are now working on this investigation,\\\" the report adds  The Department of Foreign Affairs & Trade released a statement to 7NEWS.com.au, saying they were ready to provide consular assistance to the victim.  \\\"The Australian Embassy in Paris is making urgent enquiries with French authorities following reports of an Australian citizen assaulted in Paris,\\\" a spokesperson said.  \\\"The Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade stands ready to provide consular assistance.\\\"  Other reports reveal how the woman told police she was forced to flee into a kebab shop while wearing a ripped dress and with her underwear in her hand after the alleged attack.  She also claimed they had stolen her phone.  After seeking refuge in the Dounia kebab shop on Boulevard de Clichy, near to the iconic Moulin Rouge cabaret theatre, the alleged victim was taken to Bichat hospital \\\"disoriented and unable to speak a word of French,\\\" according to other media reports.  The woman had been reportedly been in Paris for the Fete de Musique music festival but is staying in the city as the Paris Prosecutor's Office opened up an investigation into the woman's claims and began inspecting CCTV in the area.  They said in a statement: \\\"The investigation into the charge of gang rape likely to have been committed on the night of July 19 to 20 has been entrusted to the second judicial police district.\\\"  Alliance Paris Police Union added that investigators will \\\"do everything to quickly identify the individuals and bring them to justice\\\".  Security is being stepped up in Paris ahead of the Olympics which start on Friday with more than 60,000 police and soldiers, drones, helicopters and a huge increase in AI surveillance.  Fighter jets, AWACS surveillance flights, Reaper surveillance drones and helicopters with high-level snipers on board will patrol the Paris skies in France's largest deployment of troops since World War Two.  A number of safety concerns have been raised in the French capital after ISIS threatened attacks on the Olympics.  The terrorist outfit posted a propaganda poster showing one of its terrorists seemingly flying an \\\"armed drone\\\" to attack the iconic Eiffel Tower.  Officers have already made a number of arrests ahead of the Games with a 26-year-old being held for allegedly plotting \\\"violent action\\\" while a 16-year-old was also detained for allegedly saying he wanted to \\\"die a martyr\\\".  The group - calling itself the New Republican Movement   - released a chilling video earlier this week.  Jury was told\\u00a0at trial's opening today that they will be asked to decide whether his actions amounted to murder  He sprayed deodorant or perfume and he \\\"suffered a complete loss of self control and restraint and lost his temper.\\\"  Sam McCaughey has been named in court as a close associate of\\u00a0mob boss \\\"Mr Big\\\".  When called, Barry Moore said: \\\"I am not giving evidence\\\" and remained seated, looking at the ground, with his head in his left hand  The brother of feud victim Richie Carberry has become the fifth man convicted over the death of Keane Mulready-Woods.Drug dealer Stephen Carberry plead guilty to helping dispose of the teenager's dismembered body parts.Niall speaks to Eamon Dillon about how Carberry became became involved in the plot months after his brother was killed.  Ex-UVF commander Winston 'Winkie' Irvine has taken up yoga behind bars as he looks to cope with having his sentence for firearms offences doubled.\\u00a0Irvine once lived the high life, rubbing shoulders with British and Irish ministers while he negotiated on behalf of loyalists groups.\\u00a0Niall speaks to Belfast Telegraph crime correspondent Alison Morris about how Winkie now spends his days doing the 'downward dog'.  A senior garda has revealed how they made 10 'early interventions' recently to confront young people at risk of Islamic terror radicalisation.Detective Chief Superintendent Brian Woods, who heads up the Garda Special Detective Unit, made the comments as he described how the policing of terrorism has changed in Ireland.Niall speaks to Crime World's Ken Foy about how far right groups are also an increasing focus for garda\\u00ed.  Barbie Kardashian has revealed she has been contacted by gardai investigating threats issued to a prison governor.Barbie carried out a series of bizarre and sinister interviews after she was recently released from Limerick Prison.Niall speaks to Crime World's Patrick O'Connell about how Barbie's inflammatory comments could now come back to haunt her.  A notorious wife killer who murdered his wife so he could collect her life insurance policy has been moved to an open prison.Colin Whelan strangled his wife to death just months after their wedding day before pretending she had fallen down the stairs.Niall speaks to Eamon Dillon about what Whelan can expect in Loughan House Open Prison.  The trial of four men accused of torturing a man who had the word 'rat' branded on his skin has been delayed after the alleged victim failed to appear in court.Barry Moore, who is described as the principal witness in the case, failed to show up again in the Special Criminal Court, meaning the trial has now been delayed until the new year.Niall talks to Eimear Rabbitt about what comes next in the high profile case.  It's become a Christmas time regular as the Criminal Assets Bureau hold their annual auction to sell off the luxury items they have seized from criminals.Rolex and Cartier watches, Balenciaga runners as well as sunglasses and handbags all went under the hammer on Monday.Niall speaks to Crime World's Eamon Dillon about what was sold and who it had been seized from.  They are the Artificial Intelligence romance chatbots that have been accused of promoting drugs, suicide, and criminality.Online chatbots are increasingly being used by Irish teens who are struggling to connect with the opposite sex.Niall speaks to Crime World feature writer Denise Smith about how she spent a week discovering the dark side of AI chatbots.  Customer Care  Other  Privacy & Legal  News  More  Watch & Listen\"}"